This paper is about using autoencoders for collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of machine learning and information retrieval. The paper proposes a new model called RecVAE that improves upon previous models, and evaluates its performance on classical collaborative filtering datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
